01:08:34.120 --> 01:08:38.620
for a significant five figure
amount of money, which I suppose

01:08:38.620 --> 01:08:43.070
if you're building casinos or big
giant buildings with T's on them

01:08:43.070 --> 01:08:45.680
or something, $50,000
isn't a lot of money,

01:08:45.680 --> 01:08:49.780
but that was like a huge
amount of money for us.

01:08:49.780 --> 01:08:56.050
And it created a cycle that
forced us into other kinds

01:08:56.050 --> 01:08:58.870
of decisions and things
that went on.

01:08:58.870 --> 01:09:03.110
The UK magazines had a completely
different distribution model

01:09:03.110 --> 01:09:09.080
where distributors in the UK buy
the magazines and then resell them.

01:09:09.080 --> 01:09:12.730
We put -- everything that was on
newsstands was consignment for us.

01:09:12.730 --> 01:09:15.290
So when we got stiffed,
not only were we stiffed

01:09:15.290 --> 01:09:18.580
for like what didn't sell, we
were stiffed for what did sell.

01:09:18.580 --> 01:09:22.650
So it wasn't just that money

01:09:22.650 --> 01:09:24.980
that we thought was coming
in stopped coming in.

01:09:24.980 --> 01:09:30.400 position:56%
It was that money that we put out
of pocket wasn't getting reimbursed.

01:09:30.400 --> 01:09:34.760
And that set a number of
other things in motion

01:09:34.760 --> 01:09:38.000
that just weren't recoverable
for us.

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:40.380
This is also -- we're
also in a situation

01:09:40.380 --> 01:09:43.870
where Sing Out's a
folk music magazine.

01:09:43.870 --> 01:09:48.950
I mean, I wish that the publisher
of Newsweek was sitting next to me.

01:09:48.950 --> 01:09:51.350
It would help me make this case.

01:09:51.350 --> 01:09:56.430
But people share -- not only
are these direct music resources

01:09:56.430 --> 01:10:00.530
out there that if you want to
go and search them to find them,

01:10:00.530 --> 01:10:06.770
but Facebook, Myspace, Youtube,
all these places where people,

01:10:06.770 --> 01:10:09.310
the social networking stuff.

01:10:09.310 --> 01:10:13.820
So if I hear some music and I like
it, I share it with all my friends.

01:10:13.820 --> 01:10:22.580
So the response ended up -- and
there was also the emergence

01:10:22.580 --> 01:10:30.640
of content information web
development so that many

01:10:30.640 --> 01:10:35.380
of our writers like yourself,
people are writing reviews for us

01:10:35.380 --> 01:10:37.360
or writing articles for us,

01:10:37.360 --> 01:10:39.480
they just created their
own Wordpress site,

01:10:39.480 --> 01:10:42.580
and they published it themselves
and they have control over it.

01:10:42.580 --> 01:10:44.750
So there's like a ton
of those things.

01:10:44.750 --> 01:10:48.430
Now some of them we've been able
to entice those people to come

01:10:48.430 --> 01:10:52.230
and network under the Sing Out
umbrella, but many of them go well,

01:10:52.230 --> 01:10:53.530
why do I want to do that?

01:10:53.530 --> 01:10:57.040
I'll just do it myself.

01:10:57.040 --> 01:10:59.060
